20to%20infiltrate%20companies%20with%20old%20tricks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOpen-source%20models%20are%20gaining%20popularity%2C%20but%20raise%20the%20bar%20for%20cybersecurity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EResearchers%20scoured%20Hugging%20Face%20for%20malicious%20models%20and%20found%20hundreds.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20doomsayers%20continue%20to%20worry%20about%20the%20technology's%20potential%20to%20bring%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-agents-internet-dark-google-openai-anthropic-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocietal%20collapse.%3C%2Fa%3E%20But%20the%20most%20likely%20scenario%20for%20now%20is%20that%20small-time%20hackers%20will%20have%20a%20field%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHackers%20usually%20have%20three%20main%20objectives%2C%20Yuval%20Fernbach%2C%20the%20chief%20technology%20officer%20of%20machine%20learning%20operations%20at%20software%20supply%20chain%20company%20JFrog%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20They%20shut%20things%20down%2C%20they%20steal%20information%2C%20or%20they%20change%20the%20output%20of%20a%20website%20or%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhacker-online-scams-getting-worse-ai-cybersecurity-expert-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScammers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhackers-google-ai-chatbot-gemini-cyberattacks-china-iran-north-korea-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehackers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20employees%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eany%20business%2C%20are%20already%20using%20AI%20to%20jump-start%20their%20productivity.%20Yet%2C%20it's%20the%20AI%20models%20themselves%20that%20present%20a%20new%20way%20for%20bad%20actors%20to%20get%20inside%20companies%20since%20malicious%20code%20is%20easily%20hidden%20inside%20open-source%20large%20language%20models%2C%20according%20to%20Fernbach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20seeing%20many%2C%20many%20attacks%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Overloading%20a%20model%20so%20that%20it%20can%20no%20longer%20respond%20is%20particularly%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20according%20to%20JFrog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20quite%20easy%20to%20get%20to%20that%20place%20of%20a%20model%20not%20responding%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20Fernbach%20said.%20Industry%20leaders%20are%20starting%20to%20organize%20to%20cut%20down%20on%20malicious%20models.%20JFrog%20has%20a%20scanner%20product%20to%20check%20models%20before%20they%20go%20into%20production.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBut%20to%20some%20extent%20the%20responsibility%20will%20always%20be%20on%20each%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cbf1c3b5-35eb-4a4d-9fdb-7b06e2af91cc%5C%22%3EMalicious%20models%20attack%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20businesses%20want%20to%20start%20using%20AI%2C%20they%20have%20to%20pick%20a%20model%20from%20a%20company%20like%20OpenAI%2C%20Anthropic%2C%20or%20Meta%2C%20as%20most%20don't%20go%20to%20the%20immense%20expense%20of%20building%20one%20in-house%20from%20scratch.%20The%20former%20two%20firms%20offer%20proprietary%20models%20so%20the%20security%20is%20somewhat%20more%20assured.%20But%20proprietary%20models%20cost%20more%20to%20use%20and%20many%20companies%20are%20wary%20of%20sharing%20their%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoing%20with%20an%20open-source%20model%20from%20Meta%20or%20any%20one%20of%20the%20thousands%20available%20is%20increasingly%20popular.%20Companies%20can%20use%20APIs%20or%20download%20models%20and%20run%20them%20locally.%20Roughly%20half%20of%20the%20companies%20in%20a%20recent%20survey%20of%201%2C400%20businesses%20by%20JFrog%20and%20InformationWeek%20were%20running%20downloaded%20models%20on%20their%20own%20servers%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20AI%20matures%2C%20companies%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20stitch%20together%20multiple%20models%20with%20different%20skills%20and%20expertise.%20Thoroughly%20checking%20them%20all%20for%20every%20update%20runs%20counter%20to%20the%20fast%2C%20free-wheeling%20AI%20experimentation%20phase%20of%20companies%2C%20Fernbach%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20new%20model%2C%20and%20any%20updates%20of%20data%20or%20functionality%20down%20the%20road%2C%20could%20contain%20malicious%20code%20or%20simply%20a%20change%20to%20the%20model%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehackernews.com%2F2025%2F03%2Fnew-rules-file-backdoor-attack-lets.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpacts%20the%20outcome%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Fernbach%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20consequences%20of%20complacency%20can%20be%20meaningful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20a%20Canadian%20court%20ordered%20Air%20Canada%20to%20give%20a%20bereavement%20discount%20to%20a%20traveler%20who%20had%20been%20given%20incorrect%20information%20on%20how%20to%20obtain%20the%20benefit%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairline-ordered-to-compensate-passenger-misled-by-chatbot-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20company's%20chatbot%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%20after%20human%20representatives%20of%20the%20airline%20denied%20it.%20The%20airline%20had%20to%20refund%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20and%20cover%20legal%20fees.%20At%20scale%2C%20this%20kind%20of%20mistake%20could%20be%20costly%2C%20Fernbach%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbanks-ai-cybersecurity-threats-hackers-generative-ai-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBanks%20are%20already%20concerned%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20generative%20AI%20is%20advancing%20faster%20than%20they%20can%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20man%20in%20a%20black%20t-shirt%20has%20a%20conversation%20in%20a%20grey%20room%20with%20a%20JFrog%20logo%20on%20a%20screen%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d1b05a585f1dff88b1e59b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJFrog%20CTO%20Yuval%20Fernbach%20speaks%20at%20a%20company%20event%20in%20New%20York%20City%20in%20March%202025.%3Cp%3EJFrog%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20find%20out%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20problem%2C%20JFrog%20partnered%20with%20online%20repository%20for%20AI%20models%2C%20Hugging%20Face%2C%20last%20year.%20Four%20hundred%20of%20the%20more%20than%201%20million%20models%20contained%20malicious%20code%20%E2%80%94%20less%20than%201%25%20and%20about%20the%20same%20chance%20as%20landing%20four%20of%20a%20kind%20in%20a%20five-card%20hand%20of%20poker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20JFrog%20estimates%20that%20while%20the%20number%20of%20new%20models%20has%20increased%20three-fold%2C%20attacks%20increased%20seven-fold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdding%20insult%20to%20injury%2C%20many%20popular%20models%20often%20have%20malicious%20imposters%20whose%20names%20are%20slight%20misspellings%20of%20authentic%20models%20that%20tempt%20hurried%20engineers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFifty-eight%20percent%20of%20companies%20polled%20in%20the%20same%20survey%20either%20had%20no%20company%20policy%20around%20open-source%20AI%20models%20or%20didn't%20know%20if%20they%20had%20one.%20And%2068%25%20of%20responding%20companies%20had%20no%20way%20to%20review%20developers'%20model%20usage%20other%20than%20a%20manual%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20agentic%20AI%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20models%20will%20not%20only%20provide%20information%20and%20analysis%20but%20also%20perform%20tasks%2C%20and%20the%20risks%20could%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-hackers-models-hugging-face-opensource-jfrog-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743498002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67eafce169253ccddf9ad08f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-hackers-models-hugging-face-opensource-jfrog-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI%20models%20provide%20new%20opportunities%20for%20hackers%20amid%20companies'%20free-wheeling%20AI%20experimentation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ecosgrove%40businessinsider.com%20(Emma%20Cosgrove)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-hackers-models-hugging-face-opensource-jfrog-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BShocks%20Our%20Conscience%26quot%3B%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20Blasts%20Prayagraj%20Bulldozer%20Action%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EComing%20down%20heavily%20on%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20government%20and%20the%20Prayagraj%20administration%20for%20bulldozer%20action%20in%20the%20city%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20said%20the%20demolition%20drive%20was%20%26quot%3Bunconstitutional%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Binhuman%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BThis%20shocks%20our%20conscience.%20There%20is%20something%20called%20right%20to%20shelter%2C%20due%20process%20of%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20of%20Justice%20AS%20Oka%20and%20Justice%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20said%20today%2C%20while%20ordering%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20compensation%20for%20homeowners%20who%20approached%20the%20court%20for%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20court%20had%20slammed%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20government%20for%20razing%20the%20homes%20of%20a%20lawyer%2C%20a%20professor%20and%20some%20others%20without%20following%20due%20procedure.%20Advocate%20Zulfiqar%20Haider%2C%20Professor%20Ali%20Ahmed%20and%20three%20others%2C%20whose%20homes%20had%20been%20demolished%2C%20had%20told%20the%20court%20that%20they%20were%20given%20notices%20just%20one%20night%20before%20the%20bulldozer%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyer%20representing%20the%20petitioners%20had%20told%20the%20court%20that%20the%20authorities%20mistakenly%20identified%20the%20land%20on%20which%20their%20homes%20were%20built%20as%20belonging%20to%20gangster%20Atiq%20Ahmed%2C%20who%20was%20murdered%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20pulled%20up%20the%20authorities%20for%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20demolition%20notices%20were%20served.%20While%20the%20State%20counsel%20said%20the%20notices%20were%20affixed%20at%20the%20properties%2C%20the%20court%20questioned%20why%20the%20notices%20were%20sent%20by%20registered%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20affixing%20business%20must%20be%20stopped.%20They%20have%20lost%20their%20houses%20because%20of%20this...%20And%20fix%20compensation%20of%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20in%20each%20case.%20That%20is%20the%20only%20way%20to%20do%20this.%20So%20that%20this%20authority%20will%20always%20remember%20to%20follow%20due%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Oka%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20cases%20shock%20our%20conscience.%20Residential%20premises%20of%20the%20appellants%20have%20been%20high%20handedly%20demolished%20in%20matter%20which%20we%20have%20discussed%20in%20detail%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said%20in%20its%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20noted%20that%20those%20whose%20homes%20were%20demolished%20were%20not%20provided%20%26quot%3Breasonable%20opportunity%26quot%3B%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20notice.%20%26quot%3BThe%20authorities%20and%20especially%20the%20development%20authority%20must%20remember%20that%20the%20right%20to%20shelter%20is%20also%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BCarrying%20out%20demolition%20in%20such%20a%20manner%20shows%20insensitivity%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20statutory%20development%20Authority.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20referred%20to%20the%20viral%20video%20of%20a%20demolition%20drive%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh's%20Ambedkar%20Nagar%2C%20in%20which%20a%20girl%20was%20seen%20holding%20her%20books%20close%20as%20a%20bulldozer%20razed%20homes.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20is%20upset%20about%20such%20scenes%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Bhuyan%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%2