ps%3A%2F%2Fmemelibrarian.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ememe%20librarian%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIt%20allows%20for%20experimentation%20that's%20not%20tied%20to%20your%20face.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20reason%20young%20people%20are%20hanging%20out%20on%20old%20social%20platforms%20is%20that%20there's%20nowhere%20new%20to%20go.%20The%20tech%20industry%20is%20evolving%20at%20a%20slower%20pace%20than%20it%20was%20in%20the%202000s%2C%20and%20there's%20less%20room%20for%20disruption.%20Big%20Tech%20has%20a%20stranglehold%20on%20how%20we%20socialize.%20That%20leaves%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-tech-founder-gap-zuckerberg-bezos-holmes-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGen%20Z%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20scraps%20left%20by%20the%20early%20online%20millennials%20and%20attempt%20to%20craft%20them%20into%20something%20relevant.%20They%20love%20Pinterest%20(founded%20in%202010)%20and%20Snapchat%20(2011)%2C%20and%20they're%20trying%20out%20digital%20point-and-shoot%20cameras%20and%20flip%20phones%20for%20an%20early-2000s%20aesthetic%20%E2%80%94%20and%20learning%20the%20valuable%20lesson%20that%20sometimes%20we%20look%20%3Cem%3Ebetter%3C%2Fem%3E%20when%20blurrier.%20More%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20are%20signing%20up%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-yahoo-cool-again-google-meta-techlash-nostalgia-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EYahoo%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnapster-making-comeback-metaverse-music-platform-millennials-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENapster%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20surprising%20many%20people%20with%20its%20continued%20existence%2C%20just%20sold%20for%20%24207%20million.%20The%20trend%20is%20fueled%20by%20nostalgia%20for%20Y2K%20aesthetics%20and%20a%20longing%20for%20a%20time%20when%20people%20could%20make%20mistakes%20on%20the%20internet%20and%20move%20past%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20also%20brought%20more%20Gen%20Z%20users%20to%20Tumblr.%20The%20blogging%20site%20was%20an%20online%20oasis%20in%20the%20barrage%20of%20horrifying%20news%20and%20conspiracy%20theories%2C%20thanks%20to%20its%20acute%20focus%20on%20art%20and%20pop%20culture.%20And%20when%20other%20platforms%20take%20hits%2C%20Tumblr%20benefits%3A%20User%20numbers%20spiked%20to%20coincide%20with%20the%20near-banning%20of%20TikTok%20in%20January%20and%20the%20temporary%20ban%20of%20X%20in%20Brazil%20last%20year.%20Tumblr%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20refuge%20for%20people%20searching%20for%20new%20social%20sites.%20In%20January%2C%20people%20launched%20communities%20on%20Tumblr%20to%20post%20and%20preserve%20their%20favorite%20TikTok%20videos.%20Meanwhile%2C%20progressives%20mad%20at%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20and%20Elon%20Musk%20for%20going%20full%20MAGA%20and%20are%20ditching%20Facebook%20and%20X%20as%20punishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20menu%20has%20been%20full.%20There's%20been%20no%20more%20space%20to%20add%20something%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Andrew%20Roth%2C%20the%2026-year-old%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20Gen%20Z-focused%20research%20and%20consulting%20firm%20DCDX.%20In%20a%20poll%20of%20more%20than%20600%20Zoomers%20that%20DCDX%20conducted%20in%202024%2C%20two-thirds%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20wanted%20their%20social%20media%20presence%20to%20become%20more%20private.%20Tumblr%20might%20be%20just%20what%20many%20young%20people%20are%20looking%20for.%20%26quot%3BNow%20the%20time%20feels%20more%20ripe%20for%20that%20to%20happen%20for%20Tumblr%2C%20even%20if%20Tumblr%20is%20doing%20the%20same%20thing%20or%20staying%20in%20the%20same%20spot.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAri%20Levine%2C%20the%20head%20of%20brand%20partnerships%20at%20Tumblr%2C%20tells%20me%20the%20platform%20is%20both%20%26quot%3Bmore%20peaceful%26quot%3B%20and%20more%20resolutely%20itself%20than%20its%20competitors.%20While%20Meta%20runs%20around%20aping%20its%20competitors'%20features%20(reels%20from%20TikTok%2C%20stories%20from%20Snapchat)%2C%20it%20hasn't%20been%20able%20to%20mimic%20what%20Tumblr%20does%20(though%20Meta%2C%20then%20called%20Facebook%2C%20was%20in%20talks%20to%20buy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fjeffbercovici%2F2013%2F05%2F17%2Ftumblr-in-talks-with-yahoo-facebook-and-microsoft-also-said-to-be-circling%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETumblr%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20Yahoo%20did).%20%26quot%3BHow%20many%20times%20am%20I%20in%20an%20app%20and%20I%20no%20longer%20know%20what%20app%20I'm%20in%3F%26quot%3B%20Levine%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Tumblr%20still%20works%20much%20like%20an%20older%20internet%2C%20where%20people%20have%20more%20control%20over%20what%20they%20see%20and%20rely%20less%20on%20algorithms.%20%26quot%3BYou%20curate%20your%20own%20stuff%3B%20it%20takes%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20work%20to%20put%20everything%20in%20place%2C%20but%20when%20it's%20working%2C%20you%20see%20the%20content%20you%20want%20to%20see%2C%26quot%3B%20Fjodor%20Everaerts%2C%20a%2026-year-old%20in%20Belgium%20who%20has%20made%20some%20250%2C000%20posts%20since%20he%20joined%20Tumblr%20when%20he%20was%2014.%20He%20says%20he%20sees%20his%20blog%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bflow%20of%20consciousness%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bdiary%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20that's%20mostly%20made%20up%20of%20reblogging%20things%20he%20finds%20interesting%20rather%20than%20original%20posts.%20In%20a%20way%2C%20that's%20a%20core%20part%20of%20what%20Tumblr%20has%20always%20done%3A%20It's%20far%20more%20focused%20on%20fandom%20and%20art%20than%20it%20is%20around%20single%20blogs%20becoming%20cults%20of%20personality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20an%20iconic%20and%20beloved%20cultural%20corner%20doesn't%20always%20lead%20to%20cash%20flows%2C%20however%2C%20and%20the%20site%20has%20had%20a%20troubled%20decade.%20Yahoo%20bought%20Tumblr%20when%20Tumblr%20was%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20fastest-growing%20social%20networks%2C%20and%20it%20promised%20not%20to%20%26quot%3Bscrew%20it%20up.%26quot%3B%20But%20Tumblr's%20embedded%20anti-advertising%20and%20anti-influencer%20stances%20had%20driven%20a%20wedge%20between%20the%20site%20and%20monetization.%20The%20pseudonymous%20nature%20of%20Tumblr%20was%20a%20direct%20opposition%20to%20Facebook's%20insistence%20on%20users%20using%20their%20real%20names%20and%20faces%2C%20and%20the%20free-flowing%20adult%20content%20on%20the%20site%20scared%20advertisers%20off.%20Yahoo%20got%20left%20behind%20in%20the%20mobile%20revolution%2C%20and%20Tumblr%2C%20too%2C%20suffered%2C%20with%20Verizon%20scooping%20up%20both%20at%20discount.%20In%202018%2C%20Tumblr%20notoriously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftumblr-bans-nfsw-content-and-users-say-the-platform-will-suffer-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebanned%20porn%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20pissed%20off%20users%2C%20which%20led%2030%25%20of%20them%20to%20quit.%20The%20next%20year%2C%20Verizon%20offloaded%20Tumblr%20to%20WordPress'%20owner%2C%20Automattic%2C%20for%20%243%20million%2C%200.3%25%20of%20what%20Yahoo%20had%20paid%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20Automattic%2C%20Tumblr%20is%20finally%20in%20the%20home%20that%20serves%20it%2C%20Levine%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20had%20ups%20and%20downs%20along%20the%20way%2C%20but%20we're%20in%20the%20most%20interesting%20position%20and%20place%20that%20we've%20been%20in%2018%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20The%20site%20is%20trying%20to%20keep%20what%20its%20users%20love%20while%20unveiling%20features%20that%20do%20rival%20some%20of%20its%20competitors'.%20It's%20a%20shift%20after%20years%20of%20staying%20distinctly%20itself.%20In%20December%2C%20Tumblr%20launched%20its%20Communities%20feature%2C%20a%20sort%20of%20Facebook%20Groups%20meets%20subreddits%20in%20which%20people%20can%20join%20groups%20based%20on%20specific%20interests%2C%20like%20making%20art%20of%20%26quot%3Bsilly%20bugs%26quot%3B%20or%20emo%20kids%20from%20the%20Midwest.%20In%20January%2C%20Tumblr%20also%20launched%20a%20TikTok%20competitor%20called%20Tumblr%20TV%2C%20which%20works%20like%20a%20search%20engine%20for%20GIFs%20and%20supports%20videos.%20And%20following%20media%20companies%20(including%20BI)%20and%20social%20platforms%20like%20Reddit%2C%20Automattic%20in%202024%20was%20making%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftumblr-selling-user-data-ai-trianing-openai-midjourney-weird-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edeal%20with%20OpenAI%20and%20Midjourney%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20allow%20the%20systems%20to%20train%20on%20Tumblr%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Tumblr%20is%20the%2010th-most-popular%20social%20media%20site%20in%20the%20US%2C%20dwarfed%20by%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20and%20X%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20analytics%20firm%20Similarweb.%20(Tumblr%20declined%20to%20provide%20total%20user%20numbers%20to%20BI%2C%20but%20Levine%20says%20it%20has%20seen%20steady%20growth.)%20Its%20users%20see%20that%20as%20a%20pro%20rather%20than%20a%20con%3B%20it's%20more%20exclusive%20and%20intentional.%20But%20its%20history%20of%20extreme%20waves%20in%20valuation%20and%20struggles%20to%20make%20money%20may%20dictate%20its%20fate%20more%20than%20those%20who%20blog%20there.%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20Tumblr%20to%20flourish%2C%26quot%3B%20Brennan%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20it%20to%20exist%20forever.%20I%20want%20to%20use%20it%20forever.%20I%20think%20that%20it%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20beautiful%20spaces%20on%20the%20internet%20for%20someone%20to%20figure%20out%20who%20they%20are.%26quot%3B%20But%20some%20of%20Tumblr's%20model%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bblessing%20for%20it%20as%20a%20user%20is%20a%20curse%20for%20it%20as%20a%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20platform%20could%20benefit%20if%20it%20capitalized%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bshift%20from%20attention%20to%20intention%2C%26quot%3B%20Roth%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20we%20actually%20monetize%20people's%20intentions%20on%20social%20media%20versus%20the%20attention%20of%20them%20being%20around%3F%26quot%3B%20That%20would%20mean%20a%20focus%20on%20%26quot%3Bpeople's%20desires%26quot%3B%20and%20how%20to%20%26quot%3Bhelp%20them%20reach%20them.%26quot%3B%20Tumblr%20recently%20put%20out%20a%20lengthy%20report%20for%20marketers%20trying%20to%20reach%20Gen%20Z%2C%20advising%20them%20to%20engage%20with%20communities%20around%20their%20brands%20and%20to%20search%20for%20relevant%20interest%20among%20users%20over%20the%20reach%20of%20mainstream%20influencers.%20Levine%20tells%20me%20that%20when%20Automattic%20acquired%20Tumblr%2C%20it%20was%20a%20chance%20for%20the%20company%20to%20take%20%26quot%3Bstock%20of%20where%20we%20are%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Breintroduce%20ourselves%26quot%3B%20to%20users%20and%20%26quot%3Bbrands%20and%20advertisers%20who%20help%20us%20pay%20the%20bills.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETumblr%20loyalists%20tell%20me%20they%20haven't%20spent%20much%20time%20with%20the%20new%20features%20%E2%80%94%20they%20like%20the%20site%20the%20way%20it%20is.%20TJ%20Smith%2C%20a%2025-year-old%20from%20Texas%2C%20says%20it%20provided%20a%20safe%20haven%20for%20them%20when%20they%20were%2013.%20Diagnosed%20as%20autistic%20at%2011%2C%20Smith%20found%20Tumblr%20an%20easier%20place%20to%20connect%20with%20and%20talk%20about%20their%20favorite%20fandoms%2C%20like%20the%20Percy%20Jackson%20series.%20Eventually%2C%20it%20helped%20them%20work%20through%20their%20sexuality%20and%20gender%20identity%20(they%20identify%20as%20pansexual%20and%20gender%20fluid).%20%26quot%3BTumblr%20was%20the%20first%20place%20where%20I%20saw%20those%20terms%20being%20used%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20Tumblr%20blogs%20aren't%20about%20the%20people%20who%20make%20them%2C%20yet%20they're%20deeply%20personal%20places.%20Under%20their%20pseudonyms%20and%20art%2C%20people%20find%20communities%20and%20explore%20identities%20without%20scrutiny%20from%20IRL%20friends%20and%20family.%20Ashmita%20Shanthakumar%2C%20a%2025-year-old%20from%20Utah%20who%20has%20been%20on%20Tumblr%20since%202013%2C%20sees%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Banti-social%20media%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20tells%20me%2C%20and%20has%20used%20it%20to%20connect%20with%20people%20who%20like%20the%20same%20CW%20superhero%20shows%20as%20she%20did.%20She%20can%20focus%20on%20how%20the%20shows%20make%20her%20feel%20rather%20than%20personal%20updates%20on%20Facebook%2C%20which%20can%20feel%20comparative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20social%20internet%20is%20fractured.%20Millennials%20are%20running%20Reddit.%20Gen%20Xers%20and%20Baby%20Boomers%20have%20a%20home%20on%20Facebook.%20Bluesky%2C%20one%20of%20the%20new%20X%20alternatives%2C%20has%20a%20tangible%20elder-millennial%2FGen%20X%20vibe.%20Gen%20Zers%20have%20created%20social%20apps%20like%20BeReal%20and%20the%20Myspace-inspired%20Noplace%2C%20but%20they've%20so%20far%20generated%20more%20hype%20than%20influence.%20People%20of%20different%20ages%20migrate%20in%20numbers%20to%20various%20platforms%20and%20seize%20them%2C%20creating%20the%20vibes%20and%20culture%20there.%20Platforms%20lean%20more%20left%20or%20right%20politically.%20And%20while%20some%20(mostly%20on%20the%20right)%20have%20cried%20%26quot%3Becho%20chamber%26quot%3B%20with%20derision%2C%20there%20are%20benefits%20to%20carving%20out%20smaller%20communities%20with%20like-minded%20people%20to%20see%20and%20talk%20about%20the%20things%20you%20like.%20Megaplatforms%20can%20flatten%20our%20online%20experiences%20and%20reward%20content%20that%20fits%20a%20mold%3B%20smaller%20communities%20can%20enrich%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recently%20unearthed%20the%20Tumblr%20blog%20I%20made%20in%20high%20school%20(don't%20go%20looking%20%E2%80%94%20I%20deleted%20it%20and%20my%20teenage%20musings%20immediately).%20When%20I%20scrolled%20through%20Tumblr%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20at%20least%20a%20decade%2C%20I%20realized%20it%20still%20had%20something%20that%20no%20other%20social%20network%20did%3A%20the%20sense%20of%20timelessness.%20I%20saw%20a%20post%20of%20a%20simple%2C%20soothing%20color%20gradient%20followed%20by%20a%20recent%20reblog%20of%20a%20GIF%20posted%20in%202020%20but%20taken%20from%20the%202002%20original%20%26quot%3BSpider-Man%26quot%3B%20movie.%20There's%20still%20little%20video%20on%20the%20feed%2C%20and%20it's%20more%20of%20a%20silent%2C%20visual%20retreat%2C%20with%20cuts%20of%20movie%20scenes%20overlaid%20with%20dialogue%20on%20a%20loop.%20When%20I%20open%20TikTok%20and%20Instagram%2C%20I'm%20bombarded%20by%20filtered%20faces%20and%20music%2C%20or%20someone%20yelling%20into%20the%20camera%20to%20sell%20me%20a%20pair%20of%20magnetic%20eyelashes%20every%20few%20videos.%20Tumblr%20was%20the%20place%20I%20went%20in%202011%20to%20see%20and%20reblog%20flash%20photography%20and%20'90s%20movie%20GIFs%2C%20so%20it's%20no%20surprise%20that%20it's%20no%20longer%20a%20place%20where%20decades%20of%20images%20are%20juxtaposed%20together%2C%20but%20one%20that%20has%20itself%20become%20a%20piece%20of%20nostalgia%20for%20a%20simpler%20time%20online.%20Unlike%20some%20of%20its%202000s%20peers%2C%20Tumblr%20doesn't%20need%20to%20fight%20to%20get%20its%20cool%20back%2C%20but%20it%20does%20have%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20keep%20its%20cool%20and%20move%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-flocking-tumblr-millennials-musk-zuckerberg-safe-space-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743495061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67eaf9c563d72727e198c1b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-flocking-tumblr-millennials-musk-zuckerberg-safe-space-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sick%20of%20Musk%20and%20Zuckerberg%2C%20Zoomers%20have%20found%20a%20new%20place%20to%20network%20that%20millennials%20didn't%20already%20ruin%3A%20Tumblr.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Hoover)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A41%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-flocking-tumblr-millennials-musk-zuckerberg-safe-space-2025-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Reddit's%20success%20may%20be%20inextricably%20tied%20to%20Google%20Search%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224854%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Reddit%20logo%20on%20a%20phone%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Google%20logo.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67e712f963d72727e198a00e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223033%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReddit%20has%20seen%20tremendous%20growth%20since%20going%20public%20last%20year%2C%20but%20it's%20having%20difficulty%20separating%20itself%20from%20Google.%3Cp%3EOmer%20Taha%20Cetin%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EReddit%20has%20grown%20since%20going%20public%20last%20year%2C%20but%20some%20analysts%20fear%20it%20may%20be%20too%20closely%20tied%20to%20Google.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERedburn%20Atlantic%20analysts%20warned%20Reddit's%20reliance%20on%20Google%20traffic%20and%20logged-out%20users%20may%20limit%20its%20long-term%20value.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EReddit's%20stock%20has%20been%20volatile%2C%20affected%20by%20Google's%20algorithm%20changes%20and%20rumors%20of%20a%20Google%20deal.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20is%20growing%20quickly%2C%20but%20%E2%80%94%20like%20many%20media%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20struggling%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-reddit-is-taking-over-google-right-now-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseparate%20itself%20from%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWall%20Street%20analysts%20from%20Redburn%20Atlantic%20rated%20Reddit%20%26quot%3Bsell%26quot%3B%20on%20March%2017%20after%20saying%20in%20a%20note%20that%20the%20company's%20%26quot%3Bpotential%2C%20breadth%20of%20appeal%20and%20thus%20value%20as%20a%20company%20are%20being%20overstated%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2025-03-17%2Freddit-rated-sell-as-redburn-flags-risk-from-google-algorithm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Cordwell%20and%20Joseph%20Barker%2C%20analysts%20for%20the%20firm%2C%20said%20that%20much%20of%20Reddit's%20growth%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bmisconstrued%26quot%3B%20because%20it%20came%20from%20logged-out%20users%20as%20the%20main%20driver%2C%20with%20many%20of%20those%20users%20coming%20from%20Google's%20algorithm%2C%20according%20to%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20CEO%20Steve%20Huffman%20has%20repeatedly%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-google-search-ceo-steve-huffman-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20are%20going%20to%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-answers-how-it-works-performs-early-access-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintention%20of%20ending%20up%20on%20Reddit%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Redburn%20analysts%20say%20this%20trend%20could%20lead%20to%20more%20logged-out%20user%20growth%20than%20logged-in%20user%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit's%20daily%20active%20users%20who%20are%20logged%20in%20to%20their%20accounts%20were%20up%2027%25%20last%20year%2C%20but%20the%20same%20metric%20was%20up%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-mainstream-google-traffic-stock-revenue-human-users-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E70%25%20for%20people%20who%20were%20logged%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20BI%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAccelerated%20user%20growth%20has%20been%20driven%20predominantly%20by%20logged-out%20users%20who%20arrive%20on%20the%20platform%20largely%20via%20Google%20Search%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Redburn%20analysts%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThese%20users%20are%20much%20less%20valuable%20to%20Reddit%20as%20they%20are%20typically%20just%20looking%20for%20an%20answer%20to%20a%20query%20and%20thus%20spend%20little%20time%20on%20the%20platform.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECordwell%20and%20Barker%20added%20that%20there%20is%20%26quot%3Bclear%20evidence%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20boost%20to%20traffic%20from%20Reddit's%20recent%20changes%20is%20%26quot%3Bhitting%20a%20ceiling%2C%20with%20a%20risk%20that%20what%20Google%20giveth%2C%20it%20will%20taketh%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Bloomberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERedburn%20did%20not%20return%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20Reddit%20noted%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20analysts%20have%20maintained%20their%20%26quot%3Bbuy%26quot%3B%20rating%20for%20the%20company%20and%20that%20the%20experience%20for%20logged-in%20user%20has%20been%20driven%20by%20improvements%20to%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJen%20Wong%2C%20Reddit's%20COO%2C%20recently%20described%20the%20relationship%20with%20Google%20as%20%26quot%3Bsymbiotic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20using%20Google%20to%20get%20to%20Reddit%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20at%20the%20Morgan%20Stanley%20Technology%2C%20Media%2C%20and%20Telecom%20Conference%20in%20March.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20view%20it%20like%20this%2C%20I%20don't%20view%20it%20as%20existential%3B%20we%20have%20these%20two%20sources%20of%20traffic.%20It's%20not%20existential%20for%20us%2C%20but%20it%20is%20some%20chop%20that%20we%20managed%20through.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20has%20seen%20tremendous%20growth%20over%20the%20past%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddits-ipo-set-to-take-front-page-of-internet-public-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esince%20going%20public%20in%20March%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20its%20stock%20has%20seen%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-stock-drops-google-algorithm-tweak-hurt-its-user-growth-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evolatility%20in%20recent%20months%3C%2Fa%3E.%20On%20February%2012%2C%20Reddit's%20stock%20dropped%20more%20than%2015%25%20after%20Huffman%20said%20in%20an%20earnings%20call%20that%20a%20tweak%20to%20Google's%20algorithm%20caused%20%26quot%3Bvolatility%26quot%3B%20in%20site%20traffic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Btraffic%20from%20search%20has%20recovered%20so%20far%20in%20Q1%2C%20and%20we've%20regained%20momentum.%20What%20happened%20wasn't%20unusual.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2017%2C%20Reddit's%20stock%20jumped%20again%20after%20Reuters%20published%20an%20article%20that%20it%20later%20retracted%2C%20which%20said%20Google%20and%20Reddit%20had%20entered%20a%20new%20partnership.%20Reuters%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Ftechnology%2Fgoogle-expands-reddit-partnership-2025-03-17%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20update%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20post%20was%20based%20on%20outdated%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20users%20reacted%20to%20the%20post%20in%20r%2Fstock%2C%20a%20community%20where%20users%20discuss%20stocks%2C%20market%20news%2C%20and%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWild.%20There%20was%20just%20like%20a%2010%25%20pump%20and%20it%20instantly%20dropped%20back%20down.%20Is%20Wall%20Street%20Bets%20on%20this%20stock%20or%20something%3F%26quot%3B%20one%20user%20wrote%20in%20a%20comment%20about%20the%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20user%20said%20in%20the%20comments%20they%20see%20many%20Google%20search%20results%20that%20use%20Reddit%20information.%20The%20user%20wrote%20that%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Binsane%20how%20Google%20has%20basically%20sold%20out%20its%20Search%20function%20to%20operate%20as%20the%20Reddit%20search%20bar.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20of%20the%20time%20when%20you%20Google%20something%20now%20you're%20either%20shown%20a%20list%20of%20Reddit%20pages%20or%20given%20an%20AI%20overview%20that%20uses%20Reddit%20to%20write%20the%20answer%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20user%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddits-success-tied-to-google-search-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743494761000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67e7160f69253ccddf9aae83%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddits-success-tied-to-google-search-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Reddit%20has%20grown%20quickly%20since%20going%20public%20last%20year%2C%20but%20some%20analysts%20warn%20that%20its%20growth%20could%20be%20dependent%20on%20Google%20search.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kniemeyer%40insider.com%20(Kenneth%20Niemeyer)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddits-success-tied-to-google-search-2025-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Woman%20rescued%2091%20hours%20after%20Myanmar%20quake%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743494700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F25%2F04%2F1920x1080%2Fskynews-myanmar-naypyitaw-earthquake_6872754.jpg%3F20250401094741%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwoman-rescued-91-hours-after-myanmar-quake-as-number-o