e%2C%26quot%3B%20you%20might%20say%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20what's%20good%20for%20Paris%2C%20Stockholm%2C%20and%20Rome%20won't%20work%20in%20an%20American%20context.%26quot%3B%20That's%20a%20common%20refrain%20from%20skeptics%20%E2%80%94%20citing%20cultural%20differences%2C%20the%20need%20for%20abundant%20parking%2C%20or%20their%20own%20gut%20instincts%20%E2%80%94%20when%20YIMBYs%20propose%20allowing%20more%20European-style%20zoning%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20But%20these%20assumptions%20are%20incorrect%20for%20two%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20upzoning%20cities%20like%20Cambridge%20is%20not%20the%20same%20thing%20as%20requiring%20them%20to%20build%20up%20to%20Parisian%20density.%20If%20you%20own%20a%20single-family%20home%20in%20Cambridge%2C%20and%20your%20lot%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnational-zoning-map-home-prices-down-real-estate-new-houses-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupzoned%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20allow%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20four-story%20building%2C%20you%20remain%20at%20liberty%20to%20keep%20your%20single-family%20home.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20redevelop%20the%20property%20into%20a%20multifamily%20building%2C%20that's%20great%3B%20if%20you%20decide%20to%20sell%20your%20home%20to%20a%20developer%20who%20will%20replace%20it%20with%20an%20apartment%20complex%2C%20that's%20great%2C%20too.%20But%20nobody%20is%20compelling%20you%20to%20do%20either%20of%20those%20things%20if%20you%20like%20your%20existing%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20Cambridge%20%E2%80%94%20like%20many%20other%20older%20cities%20in%20New%20England%20and%20the%20mid-Atlantic%20region%20%E2%80%94%20already%20has%20a%20fair%20number%20of%20dense%20apartment%20buildings%20and%20townhomes.%20Rather%20than%20destroying%20the%20culture%20or%20character%20of%20these%20cities%2C%20building%20more%20Parisian-style%20housing%20would%20signal%20a%20return%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-cities-metro-areas-most-exclusionary-housing-zoning-policies-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20pre-single-family%20era%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Many%20of%20Cambridge's%20mid-rise%20apartment%20buildings%20were%20constructed%20before%20single-family%20zoning%20became%20ubiquitous%20in%20the%20United%20States%20in%20the%20early%2020th%20century.%20And%20the%20ones%20that%20have%20survived%20are%20now%20highly%20coveted%20as%20luxury%20homes%20and%20architectural%20treasures%3B%20yet%2C%20for%20decades%2C%20it%20has%20been%20effectively%20illegal%20to%20build%20more%20of%20them.%20As%20Azeem%20wrote%20on%20X%2C%20Cambridge's%20previous%2C%20single-family-focused%20zoning%20laws%20meant%20that%20%26quot%3B85%25%2B%20of%20the%20existing%20housing%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20city%20would%20be%20illegal%20to%20build.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20Cambridge's%20upzoning%20may%20actually%20help%20to%20preserve%20the%20city's%20architectural%20heritage%20and%20New%20England%20character.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20is%20a%20model%20for%20how%20other%20cities%20can%20upzone%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20actually%20eases%20housing%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20patchwork%20nature%20of%20American%20land-use%20policy%20can%20slow%20progress%20in%20important%20ways%2C%20it%20can%20also%20be%20an%20engine%20for%20experimentation%20and%20friendly%2C%20productive%20competition.%20Pro-housing%20activists%20in%20cities%20across%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20in%20places%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftim-walz-housing-crisis-minnesota-bringing-down-rents-prices-yimby-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMinneapolis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faustin-home-prices-falling-texas-mortgage-rates-housing-crisis-success-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAustin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.strongtowns.org%2Fjournal%2F2024%2F1%2F26%2Fsacramento-eff