3EWithin%20the%20colony%2C%20some%20individuals%20(female%20queens%20and%20male%20drones)%20are%20responsible%20for%20reproduction%2C%20while%20others%20(workers)%20are%20busy%20caring%20for%20the%20young%2C%20cleaning%20or%20foraging%20for%20food.%20Workers%20ants%20are%20always%20female.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnt%20colonies%20do%20not%20have%20leaders.%20They%20are%20an%20excellent%20example%20of%20collective%20behaviour%20and%20swarm%20intelligence%2C%20where%20individuals%20following%20relatively%20simple%20rules%20can%20collectively%20achieve%20far%20more%20than%20any%20individual%20could%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20the%20individual%20neurons%20in%20your%20brain%20can't%20compose%20music%2C%20play%20football%2C%20or%20read%20articles%2C%20the%20brain%20as%20a%20whole%20can%20achieve%20all%20these%20feats%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EColonies%20of%20co-operating%20ants%20are%20capable%20of%20amazingly%20sophisticated%20behaviours%20such%20as%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3Ebuilding%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fbeheco%2Farticle-abstract%2F26%2F1%2F223%2F2262407%3FredirectedFrom%3Dfulltext%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eefficient%20trail%20networks%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3Ebuilding%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.princeton.edu%2Fnews%2F2015%2F11%2F30%2Fants-build-living-bridges-their-bodies-speak-volumes-about-group-intelligence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliving%20bridges%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20their%20bodies%2C%20and%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%26quot%3Bfarming%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.adn7179%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efungi%20and%20aphids%3C%2Fa%3E%20(small%2C%20sap-sucking%20insects%20that%20feed%20on%20plants).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnts%20even%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2Fants-best-humans-test-collective-intelligence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutperform%3C%2Fa%3E%20humans%20on%20some%20cooperative%20cognition%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20highly%20social%20nature%20of%20ants%20is%20a%20big%20part%20of%20their%20success%20-%20and%20a%20key%20reason%20why%20they%20are%20so%20good%20at%20finding%20their%20way%20into%20our%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20colony%20contains%20thousands%20of%20intrepid%20workers%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20constantly%20searching%20for%20new%20food%20sources.%20If%20even%20a%20single%20ant%20discovers%20a%20valuable%20resource%20in%20your%20home%2C%20it%20can%20quickly%20share%20that%20information%20with%20its%20nest%20mates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDifferent%20ant%20species%20use%20different%20methods%20of%20communication%2C%20but%20the%20ones%20that%20most%20often%20invade%20our%20homes%20tend%20to%20use%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fresjournals.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1111%2Fj.1365-3032.2008.00658.x%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epheromone%20trails%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20an%20ant%20finds%20a%20food%20source%2C%20she%20returns%20to%20her%20nest%20leaving%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DJkz0L31oEZM%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elittle%20drops%20of%20pheromones%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20she%20goes%3B%20this%20trail%20guides%20other%20ants%20from%20their%20nest%20directly%20to%20the%20food%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20highly%20efficient%20communication%20system%20means%20a%20single%20ant%20can%20rapidly%20recruit%20thousands%20of%20its%20nest%20mates%20to%20any%20food%20it%20finds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnts%20may%20also%20come%20inside%20in%20search%20of%20water%2C%20particularly%20when%20the%20weather%20is%20hot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20species%20prefer%20to%20build%20their%20nests%20in%20humid%20environments%2C%20which%20might%20explain%20why%20they%20are%20often%20found%20in%20bathrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20once%20discovered%20an%20entire%20colony%20of%20sugar%20ants%20nesting%20inside%20my%20aquarium%20filter!%20The%20combination%20of%20high%20humidity%20and%20an%20enclosed%20structure%20made%20it%20an%20ideal%20place%20to%20build%20a%20nest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20heavy%20rains%20can%20flood%20ant%20nests%2C%20prompting%20colonies%20to%20seek%20drier%20ground%20-%20sometimes%20leading%20them%20straight%20into%20our%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EI%20live%20in%20an%20upper-floor%20apartment.%20How%20did%20ants%20get%20in%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20ant%20species%20are%20exceptional%20climbers%2C%20thanks%20to%20tiny%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosone%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0141269%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadhesive%3C%2Fa%3E%20pads%20and%20fine%20hairs%20on%20their%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20specialised%20structures%20allow%20ants%20to%20stick%20to%20walls%20and%20find%20footholds%20even%20on%20surfaces%20that%20appear%20smooth%20to%20the%20human%20eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemarkably%2C%20some%20canopy-dwelling%20ants%20have%20evolved%20a%20behaviour%20known%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosone%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0141269%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtrolled%20descent%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20which%20protects%20them%20when%20they%20fall.%20By%20adjusting%20the%20position%20of%20their%20abdomens%2C%20falling%20ants%20can%20steer%20their%20trajectory%2C%20directing%20themselves%20back%20toward%20the%20tree%20trunk%20and%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20do%20I%20keep%20ants%20out%20of%20my%20house%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20good%20luck.%20No%20matter%20what%20you%20do%2C%20ants%20will%20probably%20enter%20your%20house%20at%20one%20time%20or%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinding%20a%20few%20ants%20in%20your%20home%20doesn't%20mean%20your%20house%20is%20dirty.%20We%20simply%20live%20on%20a%20planet%20that%20is%20absolutely%20teeming%20with%20ants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20minimise%20unwanted%20ant%20visits%2C%20start%20by%20eliminating%20any%20potential%20food%20sources%20that%20could%20feed%20a%20hungry%20ant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStore%20all%20food%20in%20sealed%20airtight%20containers%2C%20clean%20behind%20the%20fridge%20and%20inside%2Funder%20the%20toaster%2C%20avoid%20leaving%20pet%20food%20out%20longer%20than%20needed%20and%20make%20sure%20your%20bins%20are%20securely%20sealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnts%20have%20tiny%20stomachs%2C%20so%20even%20small%20crumbs%20or%20the%20residue%20from%20spilled%20sugary%20drinks%20can%20be%20enough%20to%20entice%20them%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20ants%20seem%20to%20be%20following%20each%20other%20in%20a%20line%2C%20try%20disrupting%20their%20chemical%20trail%20using%20vinegar%20or%20bleach.%20Be%20warned%2C%20however%3A%20ants%20are%20very%20good%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphys.org%2Fnews%2F2017-10-algorithm-ants-trail-networks.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erepairing%3C%2Fa%3E%20broken%20trail%20networks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeal%20any%20small%20cracks%20or%20entrance%20points%20that%20might%20allow%20ants%20to%20get%20into%20your%20home%20and%20make%20sure%20your%20windows%20and%20doors%20have%20well-fitting%20fly%20screens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInsecticidal%20baits%20can%20kill%20ant%20colonies%2C%20but%20before%20you%20deploy%20the%20nuclear%20option%2C%20ask%20yourself%3A%20what%20harm%20are%20the%20ants%20really%20doing%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20common%20home-invading%20ants%20do%20not%20sting%20and%20are%20pretty%20harmless.%20They%20can%20usually%20be%20redirected%20simply%20by%20removing%20their